FL,304,300,200,140,000,100
PN,30302
SC,0002
CT,2,C
PS,c008
OL,0,        ECIMSBWebfax 1   F303A1776767959
OL,3,CUK unemployment drops sharply to 4.9%,
OL,4,Csurprising analysts
OL,6,FMost economists had expected the
OL,7,Fjobless rate to remain unchanged,
OL,8,FPeter Dixon, senior economist at the
OL,9,FNational Institute of Economic and
OL,10,FSocial Research, calling the drop
OL,11,F"surprising."
OL,13,FThe ONS said the fall was driven by a
OL,14,Frise in inactivity, especially among
OL,15,Fstudents, which rose 70,000 in the
OL,16,Fquarter.
OL,1,W~k4~sj5j5~s1G                    G2/8
OL,2,W/*%+,"-/.!,.!T,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,
OL,23,TppppppppppppppppppGsource: itv.com/news
OL,24,ANext Page BNat News CNat TV FClean Feed
FL,304,300,200,140,000,100
PN,30303
SC,0003
CT,2,C
PS,c008
OL,0,        ECIMSBWebfax 1   F303A1776767959
OL,3,CUK unemployment drops sharply to 4.9%,
OL,4,Csurprising analysts
OL,6,FThe figures also showed average
OL,7,Fregular wage growth dropped further,
OL,8,Fto 3.6% in the three months to
OL,9,FFebruary, down from 3.8% in the
OL,10,Fprevious three months and remaining at
OL,11,Fthe lowest level since November 2020.
OL,13,FEarnings are still outstripping
OL,14,Finflation, rising by 0.4% with the
OL,15,FConsumer Prices Index (CPI) taken into
OL,16,Faccount, but this is the lowest real
OL,17,Fgrowth for more than two-and-a-half
OL,18,Fyears.
OL,1,W~k4~sj5j5~s1G                    G3/8
OL,2,W/*%+,"-/.!,.!T,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,
OL,23,TppppppppppppppppppGsource: itv.com/news
OL,24,ANext Page BNat News CNat TV FClean Feed
FL,304,300,200,140,000,100
PN,30304
SC,0004
CT,2,C
PS,c008
OL,0,        ECIMSBWebfax 1   F303A1776767959
OL,3,CUK unemployment drops sharply to 4.9%,
OL,4,Csurprising analysts
OL,6,FVacancies also plunged by 29,000 in
OL,7,Fthe three months to 711,000 ` now the
OL,8,Flowest level since April 2021.
OL,10,FLiz McKeown, ONS director of economic
OL,11,Fstatistics, said: "Alongside falling
OL,12,Funemployment, the number of people not
OL,13,Factively seeking work increased, with
OL,14,Fdata suggesting fewer students seeking
OL,15,Fwork alongside their studies.
OL,17,F"Regular wage growth has slowed
OL,18,Ffurther with growth at its lowest rate
OL,19,Fin over five years."
